    "content_list_anbznK": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_tAWrNQ": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "",
            "description": "<p><strong>15TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Crystal<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Watch<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Ruby</p><p>Crystal catches the light differently from every angle, much like a life shared over many years. At 15 years there is history and a deeper kind of seeing. A watch marks the time passed, while ruby evokes a love still burning brightly.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>20TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> China<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Platinum<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Emerald</p><p>China is delicate, but enduring when cared for. And there’s something lovely in that to mark 20 years: the idea that precious things are made to be used, and held and looked after. Platinum represents strength and rarity, while emerald carries the feeling of renewal – proof that love can keep growing, even after so much time.<br/><br/><br/><strong>25TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Silver<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Silver<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Silver</p><p>Silver marks 25 years with classic elegance. It’s luminous without being loud, and precious without needing to be coddled. A silver anniversary is a beautiful pause: a chance to look back at the years gathered behind you, and to recognise the grace of all that has held.<br/><br/><br/><strong>30TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Pearl<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Diamond<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Pearl</p><p>Pearl returns at 30 years and it feels especially right here. Layer by layer, over time, something luminous is formed – it’s not perfect in spite of that process, but because of it. Diamonds add brightness to the milestone, but pearls give it soul: patient and intimate.</p><p></p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p><strong>15TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Crystal<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Watch<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Ruby</p><p>Crystal catches the light differently from every angle, much like a life shared over many years. At 15 years there is history and a deeper kind of seeing. A watch marks the time passed, while ruby evokes a love still burning brightly.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>20TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> China<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Platinum<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Emerald</p><p>China is delicate, but enduring when cared for. And there’s something lovely in that to mark 20 years: the idea that precious things are made to be used, and held and looked after. Platinum represents strength and rarity, while emerald carries the feeling of renewal – proof that love can keep growing, even after so much time.<br/><br/><br/><strong>25TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Silver<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Silver<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Silver</p><p>Silver marks 25 years with classic elegance. It’s luminous without being loud, and precious without needing to be coddled. A silver anniversary is a beautiful pause: a chance to look back at the years gathered behind you, and to recognise the grace of all that has held.<br/><br/><br/><strong>30TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Pearl<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Diamond<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Pearl</p><p>Pearl returns at 30 years and it feels especially right here. Layer by layer, over time, something luminous is formed – it’s not perfect in spite of that process, but because of it. Diamonds add brightness to the milestone, but pearls give it soul: patient and intimate.</p><p></p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
