    "content_list_wQQnew": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_MyRJ63": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "",
            "description": "<p><strong>35TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Coral<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Jade<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Emerald</p><p>Coral, jade and emerald each bring their own sense of life to the 35th year. There is colour and vitality, and the feeling of something still <em>moving</em>. This is a milestone for a love that has not stood still, but continued to deepen and find new forms.<br/><br/><br/><strong>40TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Ruby<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Ruby<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Ruby</p><p>Ruby is all heart. Deep red, vivid and unmistakable, it has long been tied to passion, courage and devotion. After 40 years, it feels less like a symbol of new romance and more like a tribute to love that has kept its warmth through time, change, family, memory and everything in between.<br/><br/><br/><strong>45TH ANNIVERSARY</strong><br/><br/><strong>Traditional:</strong> Sapphire<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Sapphire<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Sapphire</p><p>True blue. Sapphire is the stone of loyalty and truth, which makes it a beautiful marker for 45 years. Its blue is deep, calm and enduring, fitting for this anniversary which isn’t about spectacle, but constancy: the rare beauty of being known, and staying.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p><strong>35TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Coral<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Jade<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Emerald</p><p>Coral, jade and emerald each bring their own sense of life to the 35th year. There is colour and vitality, and the feeling of something still <em>moving</em>. This is a milestone for a love that has not stood still, but continued to deepen and find new forms.<br/><br/><br/><strong>40TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Ruby<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Ruby<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Ruby</p><p>Ruby is all heart. Deep red, vivid and unmistakable, it has long been tied to passion, courage and devotion. After 40 years, it feels less like a symbol of new romance and more like a tribute to love that has kept its warmth through time, change, family, memory and everything in between.<br/><br/><br/><strong>45TH ANNIVERSARY</strong><br/><br/><strong>Traditional:</strong> Sapphire<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Sapphire<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Sapphire</p><p>True blue. Sapphire is the stone of loyalty and truth, which makes it a beautiful marker for 45 years. Its blue is deep, calm and enduring, fitting for this anniversary which isn’t about spectacle, but constancy: the rare beauty of being known, and staying.</p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
