        "image_6eFFMi": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/OOAKV013Front.jpg",
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underCenter",
            "subheading": "<p>SAPPHIRE & DIAMOND</p>",
            "title": "<p>'Cresent Moon' Shield Ring</p>",
            "description": "<p>The crescent moon is a symbol of femininity, representing the transition from one phase of life to another. </p><p>Inspired by Warren B Davis’ artwork ‘Crescent Moon’ circa 1895, which features a poetic feminine shape, and it’s intrinsic connection to the cycles of the moon.</p><p>In ancient cultures, the crescent moon was associated with goddesses, fertility, and the cyclical nature of life, reflecting the waxing and waning phases of the moon. In vintage jewellery, this motif has a rich history of celebrating womanhood and is used within our Crescent Moon ring as an indication of the power of feminine energy. <br/><br/></p><p></p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p>The crescent moon is a symbol of femininity, representing the transition from one phase of life to another. </p><p>Inspired by Warren B Davis’ artwork ‘Crescent Moon’ circa 1895, which features a poetic feminine shape, and it’s intrinsic connection to the cycles of the moon.</p><p>In ancient cultures, the crescent moon was associated with goddesses, fertility, and the cyclical nature of life, reflecting the waxing and waning phases of the moon. In vintage jewellery, this motif has a rich history of celebrating womanhood and is used within our Crescent Moon ring as an indication of the power of feminine energy. <br/><br/></p><p></p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
