    "content_list_BPNABb": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_iPbD8U": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "",
            "description": "<p><strong>50TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Gold<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Gold<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Gold</p><p>50 years is golden for a reason – the metal holds warmth and history. It’s passed down, worn close, treasured as more than simply a celebration of years; it is a celebration of everything those years have held: the ordinary days, the defining moments, the family stories, the life built together.</p><p> </p><p><strong>55TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Emerald<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Emerald<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Emerald</p><p>Emerald marks 55 years with a real sense of growth and renewal. Its green is rich and alive, a reminder that even the longest love is not finished becoming, and honours a relationship that has continued to shift and flourish across the years.</p><p> </p><p><strong>60TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Diamond<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Diamond<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Diamond</p><p>The 60th anniversary is marked by diamond: rare, enduring and formed under time and pressure. It’s a fitting tribute to a love that has lasted not by chance, but by care; by choosing each other again and again; by making a life, and then staying to see it shine.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p><strong>1ST ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Paper<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Clocks<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Gold</p><p>The first year is still so close to the beginning, and paper feels fitting: a page, a letter, a photograph, the first chapter still being written. Clocks offer a reminder of the time you are now building together, while gold brings warmth and permanence to this earliest milestone.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>5TH ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Wood<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Silverware<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Sapphire</p><p>Wood is about roots, and five years in, a marriage has usually found some of its foundations. Sapphire, long associated with loyalty and sincerity, brings a steadiness to this anniversary.<br/><br/><br/><strong>10th ANNIVERSARY</strong></p><p><strong>Traditional:</strong> Tin or Aluminium<br/><strong>Modern:</strong> Diamond Jewellery<br/><strong>Metal or Gemstone:</strong> Diamond</p><p>Ten years deserves something with a little brilliance, and while tin and aluminium may seem like humble materials, they’re flexible, useful and enduring – qualities any long love knows well. Diamond brings the ceremony of the milestone into focus: a decade of choosing each other, and a future still opening up ahead.</p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
